    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-09-02T22:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-09-02T22:00:00-05:00" n="273"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d273">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/4020: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ruddock</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-09-03T11:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 3, 1921—11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received September 3—9:27 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>310. My 291, August 19th, 1 p.m.<note n="3" xml:id="d273fn3">Not printed.</note>
                    Wu Pei-fu successes continue, Yochow captured, Changsha threatened. Wu reported
                    planning national convention independent of Peking, Canton. Usually reliable
                    source claims Wu financed by Tsao Kun<note n="4" xml:id="d273fn4">Inspector
                        General of Chihli, Shantung, and Honan.</note> not Peking government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Ruddock</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
